bewilder his eyes.<br>
<br>
Spioctor sat and sulked the nature of the latest reports.  It seems that these new continents were much wilder, and the dangers much more diverse than what his beloved BloodTide, was used to.  The gains to be had also seemed to be much grander than previously thought, but he had seen far to many adventurers succumb to the lure of great wealth and pay the ultimate price.  We need something new, he thought, something to aid us in taming the wilds of Kuunark and the frozen tundra of Velious.<br>
<br>
&quot;back to the paperwork&quot;, he said to himself as he searched for his stamp.  Upon picking it up he glanced at the stylized double M logo of Mithaniel Marr, his most beloved diety, and to whom he had sworn an oath of eternal servitude. It bothered him that his lifelong friend Zalbar referred to his stamp as &quot;the Micky Mouse&quot; stamp, but thoughts of Zal conjured up fond memoried in the old paladins mind.  Times long past, before he had taken his sacred oath.  When he and Zal would do the things young boys reveled in.  He smiled fondly to himself as he remembered their adventures in Grobb, seducing the young trollie women and having their way with them, and fleeing the troll guards with their pants around their ankles.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, how times change&quot; he thought to himself as he remembered the scene.  <br>
<br>
Suddenly the door to his chamber was thrown wide open, with a tremendous bang.  &quot;Spio, I've just had the most wonderful revelation.&quot; His friend Zalbar stood in the doorway clutching a strange, rectangular device in his hand.  The paladin had seen the device before but knew not it's uses, only that Zalbar referred to it as a &quot;Remote&quot; and used it to assist him in his scrying of other planes with his &quot;scrying box&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;What do ya need, Zal?&quot; the paladin inquired.  He knew Zalbar had had been spendinga tremendous amount of time in his tower of late, and wondered what fanciful flights obsessed him this time.<br>
<br>
&quot;Spio i just saw the most amazing game while I was scrying the ether planes.  There were teams of large, burly men attempting to carry, kick, or throw a small object shaped much like a gnomes head to the opposing teams territory.  I think we should try something like this with the tide... It would improve moral and maybe we could get other guilds involved.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What i need you to do is gather the strongest and and most powerful in our guild so they may train and hone their tactics together. They will need to learn the new strategies of this game and how to be better than any the other guilds will be able to muster.&quot;  &quot;Oh I'll need you to gather about a dozen gnome heads so that i may perfect the making of this ball&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;You want me to order the exection of a dozen gnomes!?!, the paladin asked incredulously.<br>
<br>
&quot;hmmm, yer right....better make that an even 20 gnome heads, and be sure to cut off the noses&quot; the wizard said with a lopsided grin.  &quot;Just have &quot;the Gimp&quot; do it it if ya feel squeamish about it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Zal, I cannot order or condone the execution of gnomes...besides i don't think the gnomes would take kindly to it, and what would you do next time your &quot;scrying box&quot; goes on the fritz?&quot;   <br>
<br>
&quot;hmmm...perhaps yer right Spio, maybe it wasn't such a good idea, but damn it looks like a lot of fun.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Zal, maybe your idea isn't all that bad...we could gather the best of our forces and train them together to tackle these dungeons and monsters in these new continents.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Eh, I 'spose so, Spio.  Just draft up a charter of what ya need and I'll approve it if it seems worthy enough.  You sure you won't get me maybe just one or two gnome heads?&quot;<br>
<br>
